commit.message: removing make package.json dep on d3.vs.json, since it've been removed in the source code

Fix another rounding bug with SI-format.

Turns out 1400 * .001 is 1.4000000000000001, but 1400 / 1000 is 1.4.
biting the bullet, renaming install target to prepare (more in-line with it's meaning)
adding make prepare (which calls make install).  More inline with make traditions
add package.json dependency to make install
removing dependency on index.js: makes bootstrapping the build from git checkout much easier
Update the README to point to the Wiki.

Fix background events for d3.svg.brush.

This reverts previous IE9 fixes to @4f55282.

Revert X-Requested-With header.

Unfortunately, this breaks cross-origin requests. When the d3.xhr module is
redesigned, we'll add support for setting custom headers with requests.

Update jsdom to v0.2.14.

We can finally re-enable those tests!

Minor simplification to number regex.

If \d+\.?\d* doesn't match, then there are no digits before the "." so
no need to match \d* in the alternative pattern.

Bring area & line examples up-to-date.

Related #565.
Similar examples for area and area radial

Add example for usage of `defined` function

The `defined` function accepts a constant that is evaluated as
truthy or falsey, or a function that returns such truthy or falsey
value. If the result is truthy, then it means that datum is defined. If
falsey, then that datum is considered undefined and will not be
represented visually. This is useful in drawing multi-segmented line
or area charts, using just one SVG `<path>` directive.
